    <stitle>ANTILOCK RELAY VALVE: AR-1 - DESCRIPTION - BRAKE APPLICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BRAKE APPLICATION</title>
        <para>Brake application air enters the AR-1 service port and encounters the exhaust diaphragm, which flexes in
            response to the incoming air, sealing the exhaust passage in the cover (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0402603">Figure 3</hotlnk>
            ). Air flows around the exhaust diaphragm and moves through a passage in the cover to the top of the relay
            piston. In response to air pressure, the relay piston moves into contact with the exhaust portion of the
            inlet and exhaust valve. With the exhaust passage sealed, continued movement of the relay piston unseats the
            inlet portion of the inlet and exhaust valve, allowing supply air from the reservoir to flow out the AR-1
            delivery ports to the antilock modulators and then to the brake chambers.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0402603" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0402603" filename="../figg04/g0402603.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
